headline: Huntington Bancshares Incorporated Decreases Its Prime Rate To 7.25 Percent
summary: Huntington Bancshares Incorporated (Nasdaq: HBAN) announced that its prime rate is decreasing from 7.5 percent to 7.25 percent, effective September 18, 2025.

headline: Top Dividend Stocks To Consider Including Lakeland Financial
summary: As the U.S. market navigates the anticipation of a Federal Reserve rate cut, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average showing gains while the Nasdaq and S&P 500 experience slight declines, investors are closely monitoring how these movements might impact their portfolios. In this environment, dividend stocks can offer stability and income potential, making them an attractive option for those looking to weather market fluctuations and capitalize on consistent returns.
